Package: LargeScissor
Version: 1.0.0
Title: Large-Scale Optimized Single-Cell Identification of Subpopulations with bulk Sample phenOtype coRrelation
Authors@R: c(
    person("Duanchen", "Sun", role = "aut", email = "sund@ohsu.edu"),
    person("Xinpeng", "Li", role = c("cre", "ctb"), email = "lxpsxx@gmail.com")
  )
Maintainer: lxp <lxpsxx@gmail.com>
Description: LargeScissor is an optimized fork of the original Scissor approach. It utilizes bulk phenotypes (disease stage, survival outcomes, etc.) to identify highly phenotype-associated cell subpopulations from single-cell data. This optimized version introduces strict sparse matrix operations to prevent memory overflow (OOM) when analyzing extremely large-scale single-cell datasets (e.g., >100,000 cells) while natively supporting Gaussian, Binomial, and Cox regression models.
